{
  "texts": [
    "That is, selecting or synthetically creating specifically token-rich samples may not improve model performance.",
    "Unlike the sample size data that indicate a diminishing marginal return, the hinge model for token density shows a substantial decrease in overall performance after the EPS threshold is achieved.",
    "We note that these threshold point estimates and narrow 95% CIs converge on the average EPS (1.34) of the 2500 training sets, and this suggests that the relevant entity density of training data needs to approximate the relevant entity density of testing and production-line data.",
    "XSL • FO RenderXThis finding is especially relevant given the increasing interest in artificial training data generated by LLMs.",
    "While the insights presented here indicate that fine-tuning training data can be much smaller than generally anticipated, high-quality small training data sets still require adequate funding and time to pay, train, and deploy human annotators."
  ]
}